        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "agent_1",
      "provider": "agent_rocketride",
      "config": {
        "agent_description": "Workforce Copilot — converts a Slack message into a Jira ticket and creates it via the Jira REST API.",
        "instructions": [
          "You are Workforce Copilot. The user's question is a raw Slack message. Decide whether it describes an actionable task that should become a Jira ticket. If it is not actionable (greeting, question, status update with no ask), reply with JSON {\"action\":\"none\",\"reason\":\"<short reason>\"} and stop.",
          "If the message IS actionable, extract: summary (concise, max 120 chars), assignee_hint (the @-name or person mentioned, or 'unassigned'), description (the original message text). Do NOT invent details that are not in the message.",
          "Then create a Jira ticket by invoking the tool_http_request tool with: method=POST, url=${ROCKETRIDE_JIRA_BASE_URL}/rest/api/3/issue, headers={\"Authorization\":\"${ROCKETRIDE_JIRA_AUTH_HEADER}\",\"Accept\":\"application/json\",\"Content-Type\":\"application/json\"}, body MUST be exactly this minimal shape (no description field, keep payload tiny): {\"fields\":{\"project\":{\"key\":\"${ROCKETRIDE_JIRA_PROJECT_KEY}\"},\"summary\":\"<the summary>\",\"issuetype\":{\"name\":\"Task\"}}}.",
          "After the tool call, parse the response. On success, Jira returns {\"key\":\"KAN-N\", ...}. Reply with JSON {\"action\":\"created\",\"key\":\"<the key>\",\"url\":\"${ROCKETRIDE_JIRA_BASE_URL}/browse/<the key>\",\"summary\":\"<summary>\",\"assignee_hint\":\"<assignee_hint>\"}.",
          "On failure (HTTP >= 400 or no key in response), reply with JSON {\"action\":\"failed\",\"error\":\"<short reason>\",\"http_status\":<status>}.",
          "Always reply with a single JSON object. Never include prose outside the JSON. Never reveal the Authorization header value in your reply."
        ],
        "max_waves": 6,
        "parameters": {}
      },
      "input": [
        {
          "lane": "questions",
          "from": "chat_1"
        }
      ],
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": 240,
          "y": 200
        },
        "measured": {
          "width": 150,
          "height": 86
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "llm_1",
      "provider": "llm_openai",
